{"section": "1.4.3: If-else-statement.", "qid": 1, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n  Give your answers to the following question in numerical form (e.g., \"4\" and not \"four\").\n </p>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   2)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   <p>\n    What is the value of abs after the following lines of code are run?\n   </p>\n   <div class=\"code\">\n    <pre>x := -2\nIf ( x &gt; 0 )\n    abs := x\nElse\n    abs := -x\nEnd-if</pre>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </div>\n <div class=\"question-container flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"input\">\n   <pre><!----><textarea class=\"zb-text-area hide-scrollbar ember-text-area ember-view\" cols=\"20\" id=\"ember105\" rows=\"1\" spellcheck=\"false\"></textarea><!----></pre>\n   <div class=\"buttons flex-row\">\n    <button class=\"check-button zb-button primary raised ember-view\" id=\"ember106\">\n     <!-- -->\n     <span class=\"title\">\n      Check\n     </span>\n    </button>\n    <button class=\"show-answer-button zb-button secondary ember-view\" id=\"ember107\" style=\"\">\n     <!-- -->\n     <span class=\"title\">\n      Show answer\n     </span>\n    </button>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </div>\n</div>\n", "choices": [], "answer": "2", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation forfeit\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Answer\n </p>\n <div class=\"answers\">\n  <!-- -->\n  <span class=\"forfeit-answer\">\n   2\n  </span>\n </div>\n The condition ( x &gt; 0 ) evaluates to false because the value of x is -2. The line abs := x is skipped and the line abs := -x is executed. Therefore the final value of abs is -x, which is -(-2) = 2.\n</div>\n"}